\begin{exercise}
Derive the Fokker-Planck operator $\mathcal{L}$ for the OU process.
\end{exercise}

The Ornstein-Uhlenbeck SDE is the equation,
\begin{equation}
dX = -\gamma Xdt + \sigma dW.
\end{equation}
The corresponding Fokker-Planck equation is,
\begin{equation}
\dfrac{\partial \rho}{\partial t} = \dfrac{\partial}{\partial x}(\gamma x\rho) + \dfrac{1}{2}\dfrac{\partial^2}{\partial x^2}(\sigma^2\rho).
\end{equation}
Therefore, the Fokker-Planck operator for the OU process is
\begin{equation}
\mathcal{L}^\dagger\rho = \dfrac{\partial}{\partial x}(\gamma x\rho) + \dfrac{1}{2}\dfrac{\partial^2}{\partial x^2}(\sigma^2\rho).
\end{equation}

